<h1 class="hero-h">How a 12-person SaaS team <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">cut proposal time 70%.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">A B2B SaaS company with 12 people including 4 in revenue. Proposals were eating senior time and slowing deal velocity. After a Treetop Implementation engagement, the proposal cycle compressed dramatically. Here is what happened.</p>
<div class="headline-metric">
<div class="metric-num">70%</div>
<div class="metric-label">reduction in proposal turnaround time, sustained 6+ months post-engagement</div>
</div>
<div class="disclosure"><p>Composite case study: a synthesis of patterns we have seen repeatedly across similar engagements. Specific names, numbers, and details are illustrative; the patterns and outcomes reflect real client results.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">The starting situation</span><h2 class="h2">Before</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>Company stage:</strong> 12 employees, ~$3M ARR, B2B SaaS selling to mid-market.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Proposal volume:</strong> ~10 proposals per month, $30K-$120K ACV each.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Pain:</strong> Each proposal took 6-8 hours of senior team time (CEO or VP Sales). Deals stalled while waiting for proposals. Sales velocity capped by writing capacity.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Existing AI usage:</strong> ChatGPT Plus for one or two people, used inconsistently.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">The intervention</span><h2 class="h2">What Treetop built</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>Week 1:</strong> Operational ICP definition. Audit of existing proposal templates and last 10 winning proposals.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Week 2:</strong> Built a Proposal Claude Project loaded with: 10 winning proposals (anonymized), brand voice guide, pricing reference, standard scope language, common objection responses.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Week 3:</strong> System prompt iterated until proposals matched winning voice. Trained the team (CEO, VP Sales, 2 AEs) on the workflow.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Week 4:</strong> Shipped 4 real proposals using the new workflow. Refined based on what worked.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">What changed</span><h2 class="h2">The new workflow</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>Old workflow:</strong> AE takes discovery notes → drafts 6-hour proposal → CEO/VP Sales reviews and rewrites → ships in 2-3 days.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>New workflow:</strong> AE pastes discovery notes into Proposal Project → Claude drafts in 5 minutes → AE refines for 30 minutes → senior reviewer does 15-minute polish → ships same day.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Quality:</strong> Win rate stayed flat in months 1-2, then increased 8% in months 3-6 as the team's editorial muscle developed for prioritizing the highest-leverage sections.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">The lasting changes</span><h2 class="h2">6 months later</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>Time savings:</strong> Roughly 50 hours/month of senior team time recovered.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Sales velocity:</strong> Average sales cycle compressed from 35 days to 24 days because proposals shipped within hours of qualified opportunity.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Capacity:</strong> Without adding headcount, the team supported 60% more outbound activity because proposal-writing was no longer the bottleneck.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Investment:</strong> $3,500 Implementation + $300/month Claude Team for 10 seats. Total first-year cost: ~$7,000. Estimated value recovered: $150,000+ in senior time freed.</p>
    </div></section>

